  "texts": [
    "The DL approach performed equally well as geometric morphometrics and provided an extensive reference dataset, including fossil teeth; it successfully identified teeth from an archaeological deposit that was not included in the training dataset.",
    "However, the model's ability to classify fossil teeth against modern specimens is limited by taphonomic alterations and differences in presentation, such as background and coloration, making direct between extant and extinct taxa comparison challenging.",
    "Additionally, the lack of morphological feedback from DL models hinders the enrichment of traditional taxonomic keys, as these models operate as 'black boxes' without clear insight into the discriminative features used.",
    "Pizarro-Monzo et al. (2023) introduce a DL approach for distinguishing between anthropogenic and non-anthropogenic bone surface modifications in the Late Pleistocene Toll Cave site.",
    "The core novelty lies in using TL with three different CNN architectures: ResNet50, VGG19, and DenseNet201, which were adapted to classify cut-marks, carnivore scores, and trampling striations."
  ],
